        <title><m>\S IV.5</m>: Limits, Bounds, and <m>\R</m></title>
            <page>
                <exercise workspace="1in">
                    <title>Motivation: Limits and Bounds  </title>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            Last time we explored different ways that sequences converged. We'll use the concepts
                            of monotone and bounded to say more about when sequences converge.
                        </p>
                    </solution>
                    
                
                </exercise>
                <exercise workspace="6in">
                    <title>Practice: Monotone, bounded, and convergence</title>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            Do you think the following implications are true or false? If false, describe a counter-example.
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        If <m>(a_i)</m> converges, then it is bounded.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        If <m>(a_i)</m> is bounded, then it converges.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        If <m>(a_i)</m> converges, then it is monotone.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        If <m>(a_i)</m> is monotone, then it converges.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        If <m>(a_i)</m> is monotone and bounded, then it converges.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </p>

                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            <ol>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        This is true.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        This is false. Consider <m>a_i = (-1)^i</m>.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        This is false. Consider <m>a_i = \frac{(-1)^i}{i}</m>.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        This is false. Consider <m>a_i = 2^i</m>.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        This is true, and can be a very useful fact for analyzing recursive sequences.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </p>
                    </solution>
                    
                    
                </exercise>

            </page>
